@foxx making us easier to find would be awesome :) I'm all for improving the README. Will need to think about renaming the repo a bit tho.

I quite like what the requests crew did with docs.python-requests.org. Maybe we can do something similar? Aim to have readthedocs be the main landing site but with obvious links to the github page. It would require rebranding https://oauthlib.readthedocs.org/en/latest/ to be more than just a random docs dump of course.

I already own oauthlib.com/org since before but went ahead and registered python-oauth.com/org, python-oauth2.com/org as well as python-oauthlib.com/org. Happy to point them wherever but maybe aim to just promote one of them? Not sure which one :)
